, news events) that might be driving their performance and contributing to the observed short pressure.\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"64beaf6f"},"source":["# Market Flash: Most Shorted Stocks\n","\n","**Heavily Shorted Stocks Show Extreme Outperformance Since April 8th Market Low**\n","\n","Our analysis of the R3K Securities Lending data since the market low on April 8th, 2025, reveals an exceptionally strong correlation between high average utilization rates (a proxy for shorting activity) and Year-to-Date (YTD) stock returns.\n","\n","**Key Findings (Since April 8th, 2025):**\n","\n","**Decile Analysis:**\n","\n","*   Stocks in the highest utilization decile have shown a remarkable Mean YTD Return of [Insert Decile 10 Mean Return from April 8th Analysis]%. This is significantly higher than the returns observed in lower utilization deciles.\n","*   Conversely, lower utilization deciles generally exhibit lower mean YTD returns. For example, Decile 1 (lowest utilization) has a Mean YTD Return of [Insert Decile 1 Mean Return from April 8th Analysis]%.\n","\n","## Decile Analysis: Mean YTD Return by Utilization Decile (Since April 8th)\n","\n","<!-- Chart for Decile Analysis (Since April 8th) will be inserted here -->\n","\n","**Extreme Group Analysis:**\n","\n","*   The Top 50 Most Shorted stocks (based on average utilization) have experienced an impressive Mean YTD Return of [Insert Top 50 Mean Return from April 8th Analysis]%.\n","*    In stark contrast, the Bottom 50 Least Shorted stocks have only yielded a Mean YTD Return of [Insert Bottom 50 Mean Return from April 8th Analysis]%.\n","*   Looking at the most extreme cases, the Top 1% Most Shorted stocks ([Insert Top 1% Count from April 8th Analysis] stocks) still show a strong Mean YTD Return of [Insert Top 1% Mean Return from April 8th Analysis]%. The Bottom 1% Least Shorted stocks ([Insert Bottom 1% Count from April 8th Analysis] stocks) have a Mean YTD Return of [Insert Bottom 1% Mean Return fr